            "title": "Natural Pearls",
            "description": "We use baroque and freshwater pearls — each one uniquely shaped by nature over months of slow growth inside a living mollusk. China produces over 95% of the world's freshwater pearls, primarily from farms in Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces. We source from small-batch farms in these regions that prioritize individual cultivation over industrial volume. You'll notice variations in form, size, and luster — that's not a flaw, it's proof of authenticity. Our freshwater pearls are selected for their organic beauty and soft, natural glow. In many traditions, pearls symbolize wisdom, calm, and quiet strength.",
            "link_url": "/collections/all",
            "link_text": "Shop Pearl Bracelets"
          }
        },
        "stones": {
          "type": "material_card",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/ac7c941f089f2cc721d9bd5bece2d52b.png",
            "title": "Gemstones",
            "description": "Amethyst, red agate, tiger's eye, lapis lazuli, citrine, black agate, clear quartz — hand-cut and minimally polished to preserve natural texture and inclusions. Each stone comes from a region known for that specific mineral: amethyst from Brazil's Rio Grande do Sul, where volcanic basalt deposits produce roughly 60% of the world's supply. Lapis lazuli from Afghanistan, prized for millennia for its deep blue. Tiger's eye from South Africa's Northern Cape, where it forms in layers of iron-rich sedimentary rock. Red and banded agate from India and Madagascar. We source stones that show character, not factory uniformity. No stone is dyed, heated, or coated — what you see is what nature made.",
            "link_url": "/collections/all",
            "link_text": "Explore Gemstone Bracelets"
          }
        },
        "silver": {
          "type": "material_card",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/logo.jpg",
            "title": "S925 Sterling Silver",
            "description": "All metal components — spacers, logo tags, and the small maker's mark on every strand — are crafted from S925 sterling silver: an alloy of 92.5% pure silver and 7.5% copper, the international standard for fine silver jewelry. The copper adds the durability that pure silver lacks, making it strong enough for daily wear without sacrificing its natural luster. Each piece is hand-finished for a smooth feel against the skin. Over time, sterling silver develops a gentle patina — a sign of a piece that's genuinely lived in.",
            "link_url": "/pages/client-care#care",
            "link_text": "Sterling Silver Care Guide"
