        "body": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We work with a small network of stone suppliers and pearl farms — relationships built over years, not transactions. We don't own farms or mines. Instead, we partner with suppliers in specific regions who share our standard: natural formation, no chemical treatment, no shortcuts.</p><p>Our freshwater pearls come from farms in China's Zhejiang province, where environmental regulations introduced between 2015 and 2020 significantly raised cultivation standards across the industry. Our gemstones are sourced from regions renowned for each specific mineral — not because it's romantic, but because geology determines quality. Brazilian amethyst has a depth of color that other origins can't match. Afghan lapis lazuli has been traded along the same routes for over 6,000 years. South African tiger's eye forms in banded iron formations found almost nowhere else on earth.</p><p>Nothing we use is dyed, heated, irradiated, or coated to change its appearance. Every order ships with a certificate of authenticity — because when we say natural, we mean it.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "narrow",
            "alignment": "center",
