        "body": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Natural Gemstones:</strong> Wipe gently with a soft, dry cloth after wearing. Avoid prolonged contact with perfume, lotion, or chlorinated water. Stones like amethyst and lapis lazuli can fade with extended UV exposure — store your gemstone bracelet in its box or a soft pouch when not wearing it.</p><p><strong>Freshwater Pearls:</strong> Pearls are organic and porous — they absorb what touches them. Put your pearl bracelet on last, after cosmetics and fragrance have dried. A light wipe with a barely damp cloth after wearing keeps their luster. Store separately to prevent scratching from harder stones or metals.</p><p><strong>S925 Sterling Silver:</strong> Sterling silver may darken naturally over time through oxidation — the copper in the alloy reacting with air and moisture. A gentle polish with a silver cloth restores its brightness in seconds. Many of our customers prefer the warm patina that develops with daily wear.</p><p>For sizing, shipping, and returns, visit our <a href=\"/pages/client-care\">Client Care</a> page.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "narrow",
            "alignment": "center",
